    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1964-04-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1964-04-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="166"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d166">
                <head>166. Memorandum From <persName corresp="#p_BWH_1">William H.
                        Brubeck</persName> of the National Security Council Staff to President
                        <persName corresp="#p_JLB_1">Johnson</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d166fn1">Source: <persName corresp="#p_JLB_1"
                            >Johnson</persName> Library, National Security File, Country File,
                        Congo, Vol. I. Secret.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1964-04-20">April 20, 1964</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Attached are Averell <persName corresp="#p_HWA_1">Harriman</persName>’s specific
                    recommendations for increased military assistance to the Congo, based on his
                    recent trip, and with Defense and <gloss target="#t_AID_1">AID</gloss>
                        concurrence.<note n="2" xml:id="d166fn2">Not attached. A copy of <persName
                            corresp="#p_HWA_1">Harriman</persName>’s April 20 memorandum to the
                        President is in National Archives, <gloss target="#t_RG_1">RG</gloss> 59,
                        Central Files 1964–66, DEF 19 US–THE CONGO.</note> This program will add
                    $5.1 million fiscal 1964 funds to the $3.5 million per year already programmed
                    for <gloss target="#t_FY_1">FY</gloss> 1964 and <gloss target="#t_FY_1"
                        >FY</gloss> 1965.</p>
                <p>Main points of the program:</p>
                <p>1. Funds are almost all for combat air and airlift capacity—</p>
                <p>six T28C fighter aircraft</p>
                <p>six H21 coup lift helicopters</p>
                <p>ten C47 aircraft</p>
                <p>aircraft operation and maintenance costs</p>
                <p>2. We will try to get the Belgians to operate these aircraft; if unsuccessful we
                    will try a civilian contract operation; but in any event US military will not
                    take an operational flight or ground crew function.</p>
                <p>3. Additional aid may be required if the Congo situation worsens.</p>
                <pb facs="0269" n="236" xml:id="pg_236"/>
                <p>4. If <persName corresp="#p_ACY_1">Adoula</persName> requests temporary loan of
                    military security forces from other Africans (e.g. Nigerians) we may have to
                    contribute to cost.</p>
                <p>Recommendation: That you approve the program as outlined above.<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d166fn3">President <persName corresp="#p_JLB_1">Johnson</persName>
                        initialed his approval of the recommendation.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>B.<note n="4" xml:id="d166fn4">
                            <persName corresp="#p_BMG_1">McGeorge Bundy</persName> initialed under
                                <persName corresp="#p_BWH_1">Brubeck</persName>’s initial.</note>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
